When compiling:

``` rust
use std::ops::{Add};

pub struct Vector2<T> {
    pub elems: [T; 2],
}

impl <U, T: Add<U>> Add for Vector2<T> {
    pub fn add(self, rhs: &Vector2<U>) -> Vector2<Add<U>::Output> {
    }
}
```

I didn't intend to specify a default type for T, but wanted a trait constraint on `Add<U>`. Just writing `Add` fixes the warning, the rest stays the same. Also note how rustc crashes with SIGILL before printing how rustc panicked (I can't get a backtrace this way, and it happens independent of the value of `RUST_BACKTRACE`).

